        <p><strong>Computer hardware</strong> is the collection of physical elements that constitutes a computer system.</p>
        <p>Computer hardware refers to the physical parts or components of a computer such as the monitor, mouse, keyboard, computer data storage, hard drive disk (HDD), system unit (graphic cards, sound cards, memory, motherboard and chips), etc. all of which are physical objects that can be touched.</p>
        <p>In contrast, {'software'|link_urls:'i'} is instructions that can be stored and run by hardware.</p>
        <p>Software is any set of machine-readable instructions that directs a computer's processor to perform specific operations.</p>
        <p>A combination of hardware and software forms a usable computing system.</p>
